## 3. Memory Strategy

Mastra provides four memory layers. We use all four, scoped to HobbyFi's needs:

### Memory Scoping Rules (HobbyFi specific)

| What | Scope | Storage | Retention |
|---|---|---|---|
| Conversation turns | `thread_id = conversation_id` | PostgreSQL | Session lifetime + 30 days |
| Working Memory (vendor context) | `resource_id = vendor_id` | PostgreSQL / Upstash | Until vendor clears or changes tracks |
| In-flight proposed diffs | `thread_id` | Redis (TTL 1hr) + PostgreSQL audit log | Redis: 1hr; Audit log: indefinite |
| Semantic Recall embeddings | `resource_id = vendor_id` | PostgreSQL pgvector | Indefinite (Phase 2 full rollout) |

