## 5. Workflow Orchestration

### Orchestration Engine: Mastra Workflows

Mastra's graph-based workflow engine (`.then()`, `.branch()`, `.parallel()`, `.suspend()`, `.resume()`) replaces a hand-rolled orchestration loop. Both the read and write flows are modeled as Mastra workflows.

### Read Workflow

```
mastra.createWorkflow("copilot-read")
  .step("load-session-memory")        // Fetches conversation history + working memory
  .step("build-system-prompt")        // Track-aware prompt construction
  .step("run-agent")                  // Gemini + tool-calling loop (may call multiple tools)
  .step("format-response")            // Compose answer + deep-link URL
  .step("persist-turn")               // Save turn to thread store
  .step("stream-to-client")
```

### Write Workflow (Approval-Gated with Suspend/Resume)

```
mastra.createWorkflow("copilot-write")
  .step("load-session-memory")
  .step("resolve-entity")             // find_user / validate record ownership
  .branch({
    "ambiguous": .step("ask-clarifying-question").suspend("awaiting-clarification"),
    "resolved":  .step("build-diff")  // Call write tool → returns ProposedDiff
  })
  .step("create-audit-entry")         // INSERT copilot_audit_log status=proposed
  .step("render-diff-card")           // Stream DiffCard to frontend
  .suspend("awaiting-approval")       // ← Mastra SUSPENDS here; state saved to PostgreSQL
                                      //   Workflow can be resumed days later if needed

  // ── Vendor taps Approve / Edit / Reject in UI ──────────────────────────
  // Resume triggered by POST /copilot/actions/:id/approve or /reject

  .branch({
    "rejected": .step("mark-rejected").step("notify-vendor"),
    "approved": .step("re-validate-diff")   // Stale diff check
      .branch({
        "stale":   .step("re-propose"),     // Re-suspend for new approval
        "fresh":   .step("execute-action")  // Call portal service stub
          .step("mark-executed")            // UPDATE audit log status=executed
          .step("stream-confirmation")
      })
  })
```

