## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Mastra server deployment** — Mastra's workflow engine requires a persistent process (Node.js server) to handle suspend/resume state. The `apps/mastra` package will run as a standalone Express/Fastify server. Next.js API routes in `apps/portal` act as the BFF/Gateway and proxy to the Mastra server. Confirm this split is acceptable, or if you'd prefer everything in a single Next.js process.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **PostgreSQL pgvector for semantic recall** — Semantic recall (Layer 3 memory) requires the `pgvector` extension on your PostgreSQL instance. This is available on Supabase, Neon, Railway, and self-hosted PG 15+. Confirm your DB hosting supports pgvector, or we can skip semantic recall for Phase 1 and enable it in Phase 2.

> [!WARNING]
> **Mock portal services** — `execute_action` will call stub implementations of the booking/membership services in Phase 1. Real integration with HobbyFi's production services needs to happen before go-live. We need the internal API specs for: trial extension, membership date update, no-show mark, booking cancellation.

